CHANGE CONTROL (MUST FOLLOW):
- Do not refactor or rename existing functions that already passed tests.
- Do not modify lib/rotation.ts algorithm behavior unless explicitly instructed.
- Any change must be minimal and localized to the specified files only.
- Provide a diff-style summary: files changed + what lines/sections changed + why.
- If you think a refactor is needed, STOP and propose it first (do not do it).

Timezone Architecture Rule (Non-negotiable)
Parallel must use IANA timezones as the single source of truth.
Rules:
1. All members must store timezone as an IANA string
   Example:
   America/New_York
   Europe/London
   Asia/Tokyo
2. timezone_offset must NOT be used for any logic.
   It may exist temporarily for legacy migration only.
3. All time calculations must follow this pipeline:
    UTC time
   → convert using member.timezone (IANA)
   → produce localStart / localEnd
   → compute burden / fairness
4. UI display timezone must default to owner.timezone.
5. displayTimezone must never change automatically when toggling UI states
   (e.g. enabling/disabling fixed base time).
6. Offsets must NEVER be stored or trusted as the source of truth.
   Offsets can only be derived dynamically from IANA timezone when needed for display.
7. Any function converting timezone must accept IANA timezone only.

Code Stability Rule
Do NOT modify the following systems unless explicitly instructed:

- rotation scoring algorithm
- beam search logic
- fairness spread calculation
- invariant validation logic

Changes in this phase must ONLY affect:
- timezone data model
- timezone conversion helpers
- UI display timezone default behavior

All algorithm outputs must remain identical before and after this change.

In Parallel scheduling: hardNoRanges are the only hard constraint. Working hours are soft and affect burden only. In Anchor mode (useFixedBaseTime=true), the planner must schedule exactly at the user-selected base time unless it intersects any hard boundary; it must never replace the chosen base time with a lower-burden in-working-hours time. Always inject baseTimeMinutes into candidate generation and log whether it was considered/rejected.
